        "title": "1. `models.py` — Job / parse_posted_at",
        "content": "\nUntested: `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`.\n\nKey gaps:\n- No test proves `content_hash` is **insensitive to `salary_range` and `posted_at`** — meaning a comp change alone will never be detected as a \"changed\" job by `Store.diff`. That's a real behavioral edge case worth locking down explicitly (whether intentional or not).\n- Workday's `posted_at` (\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is prose the docstring calls out, but `parse_posted_at` has no prose-parsing branch — it silently returns `None`. Nothing currently pins this down, so a future refactor could \"fix\" it and change filtering behavior for every Workday source without anyone noticing.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt == datetime.fromtimestamp(1643241332.430, tz=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso_with_z(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-01T00:00:00\").tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_is_unparseable(self):\n        # documents current (intentional?) behavior: filters.match() treats\n        # this as \"keep, can't confirm age\" rather than crashing\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_garbage_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not-a-date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def test_key_stable_across_title_change(self, make_job):\n        j1 = make_job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        j2 = make_job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self, make_job):\n        assert make_job(title=\"A\").content_hash != make_job(title=\"B\").content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_salary_and_posted_at(self, make_job):\n        j1 = make_job(salary_range=\"100k\", posted_at=\"2024-01-01\")\n        j2 = make_job(salary_range=\"200k\", posted_at=\"2025-01-01\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash  # documents the gap above\n\n    def test_to_row_strips_raw_adds_key_and_hash(self, make_job):\n        row = make_job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert \"key\" in row and \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n---\n\n",
