        "title": "3. `filters.py` — match / filter_jobs",
        "content": "\nUntested entirely. Key edge cases: word-boundary regex behavior, `None` vs `[]` for optional filter lists, and the \"keep unparseable dates\" rule.\n\n```python\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\nfrom models import Job\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_filters_passes(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job()) is True\n\n    def test_exclude_blocks(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"Senior Recruiter\"), exclude=[\"recruiter\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_word_boundary_java_does_not_match_javascript(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"JavaScript Engineer\"), include=[\"java\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_none_means_no_filter(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job(title=\"anything\"), include=None) is True\n\n    def test_locations_empty_list_is_no_filter(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"\"), locations=[]) is True\n\n    def test_locations_no_match_excludes(self, make_job):\n        assert match(make_job(location=\"Berlin\"), locations=[\"NYC\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self, make_job):\n        j = make_job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n        assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc)) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_excludes_older_job(self, make_job):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n        j = make_job(posted_at=old)\n        assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_newer_job(self, make_job):\n        j = make_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_computes_cutoff(self, make_job):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n        jobs = [make_job(posted_at=old)]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": 5}) == []\n\n    def test_empty_rules_dict_passes_everything(self, make_job):\n        assert filter_jobs([make_job()], {}) == [make_job()]\n```\n\n---\n\n",
