        "title": "6. `fetchers.py` — largest untested surface (787 lines, ~30 functions)",
        "content": "\nThis is the highest-risk module because every `parse_*` function encodes undocumented, brittle assumptions about third-party JSON/HTML shapes. Group by pattern rather than writing 15 near-identical blocks:\n\n**A. Retry/transport layer (`_request`) — test in isolation with `respx` or a hand-rolled `httpx.MockTransport`:**\n\n```python\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_retries_on_retryable_status_then_succeeds(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.asyncio.sleep\", AsyncMock())  # skip real backoff\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(503)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x\")\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_raises_runtime_error(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.asyncio.sleep\", AsyncMock())\n    async def always_503(request): return httpx.Response(503)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(always_503)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_non_retryable_404_still_gets_retried_before_failing(monkeypatch):\n    # documents a real inefficiency: raise_for_status() raises HTTPStatusError\n    # for ANY 4xx, which the except clause catches and retries needlessly\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.asyncio.sleep\", AsyncMock())\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x\", retries=3)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 3  # wasted retries on a permanent error\n```\n\n**B. Parser normalization functions — pure functions, no network, cheapest to test.** For each of `parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever`, `parse_ashby`, `parse_smartrecruiters`, `parse_recruitee`, `parse_workable`, `parse_google`, `parse_deshaw`, `parse_twosigma`, `parse_optiver`, `parse_meta`, `parse_microsoft`, `parse_netflix`, `parse_amazon`, apply this shared skeleton shape (only `parse_lever` shown fully; repeat per-source with that source's own defensive-default fields):\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import parse_lever, _lever_salary\n\nclass TestParseLever:\n    def test_normal_payload(self):\n        data = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"text\": \"Engineer\", \"hostedUrl\": \"https://x\",\n                 \"categories\": {\"location\": \"NYC\", \"team\": \"Eng\", \"commitment\": \"FT\"},\n                 \"createdAt\": 1700000000000}]\n        jobs = parse_lever(\"acme\", data)\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"NYC\" and jobs[0].employment_type == \"FT\"\n\n    def test_missing_categories_defaults_empty(self):\n        jobs = parse_lever(\"acme\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"text\": \"E\", \"hostedUrl\": \"u\"}])\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_min_max_formats_with_commas(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}) \\\n            == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_plain_description(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_neither_present_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n```\n\nHighest-value edge cases per remaining parser (currently zero coverage on any of these):\n- `parse_ashby`: `isListed is False` jobs must be filtered out; `id` vs `jobId` fallback.\n- `parse_google` / `_extract_ds1`: primary regex miss falling through to the fallback regex; invalid embedded JSON returning `[]`; `job[0]` falsy entries skipped; out-of-range index access on short arrays.\n- `_ds1_posted_at`: preference order index 12 → 13 → 14; all absent → `\"\"`.\n- `parse_deshaw` / `parse_twosigma`: dedup of repeated cards/anchors (both explicitly documented as rendering the same job 2–3x); location lookup window bounded to the next anchor.\n- `_amazon_posted_at`: valid `\"June 26, 2026\"` string; malformed string and unknown month name both degrading to `\"\"` via caught `ValueError`/`KeyError` (currently no test proves the except clause is reachable at all).\n- `parse_meta`: dedup by id; blank id skipped; token-scraping regexes (`lsd`, `__spin_r`, `__spin_b`, `__spin_t`) with `\"for (;;);\"` XSSI prefix stripped before JSON parse; `data[\"errors\"]` triggers `RuntimeError` (simulates a rotated `doc_id`, the failure mode the module docstring explicitly warns about).\n\n**C. Pagination fetchers (`fetch_workday`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_meta`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`) — need `httpx.MockTransport` sequencing multiple responses:**\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_at_total_and_respects_5000_cap(monkeypatch):\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": \"E\",\n            \"externalPath\": \"/job/1\", \"bulletFields\": [\"R1\"]}], \"total\": 1})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\"})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1  # loop must stop once offset >= total, not loop forever\n```\n\nApply the same \"stop on no-fresh-page\" + \"respect max_pages\" pattern to each of the other seven pagination fetchers — none currently prove the pagination loop actually terminates, which matters given several have safety caps in the dozens of pages.\n\n**D. Registry / dispatch:**\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\nimport pytest\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror():\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n        await fetch_source(None, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_one_source_failing_does_not_abort_others(monkeypatch):\n    async def fake_fetch_source(client, src):\n        if src[\"ats\"] == \"boom\": raise RuntimeError(\"down\")\n        return [Job(source=\"x\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"t\", url=\"u\")]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.fetch_source\", fake_fetch_source)\n    jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"boom\", \"company\": \"b\"}, {\"ats\": \"ok\", \"company\": \"c\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_reuses_injected_client_without_closing_it():\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n    await fetch_all([], client=client)\n    assert not client.is_closed\n    await client.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "7. `agent.py` — CLI + deterministic helpers + PDF rendering",
        "content": "\nUntested entirely.\n\n```python\nfrom agent import cmd_db_new, cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats\nimport json\n\nclass TestDbNew:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, tmp_path, capsys, make_job):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\nsources: []\")\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\") as s:\n            s.diff([make_job()])\n        cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True and out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(self, tmp_path, capsys, make_job):\n        # rows sharing one first_seen timestamp must never be split by --limit\n        ...\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_invalid_watermark_returns_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\nsources: []\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n    def test_neither_watermark_nor_now_returns_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"; cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\nsources: []\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_smart_quotes_in_body(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\")\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in html and counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 1\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks(self):\n        html, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>a\\u2014b</p>\")\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in html  # inside <style>, untouched\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1  # only the <p> occurrence counted\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html, _ = _normalize_ats('<a title=\"x\\u2014y\">a\\u2014b</a>')\n        assert 'title=\"x\\u2014y\"' in html  # attribute preserved\n```\n\nAlso missing: `cmd_pdf_render` (missing-input-file → return 2; `%PDF` magic-byte failure path → return 1; CSS injected before `</head>` vs. prepended when no `<head>` exists — needs `subprocess.run` mocked, no real Chrome dependency), `_chrome_bin` (CHROME_PATH env precedence → `shutil.which` → hardcoded app paths → `sys.exit`), and `main()`'s argv-splitting logic (mode words vs. passthrough flags, `-i`/`--interactive` detection).\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
