      {
        "title": "Integration test gaps",
        "content": "\nNo test currently exercises more than one module together. Worth one end-to-end test:\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_pipeline_end_to_end_greenhouse_to_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    \"\"\"fetch (mocked HTTP) -> filter -> store.diff -> dispatch, real SQLite.\"\"\"\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"\"\"\nsources: [{{ats: greenhouse, company: acme}}]\nfilters: {{include_keywords: [engineer]}}\ndb: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\n\"\"\")\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [\n            {\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Software Engineer\", \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\"}]})\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"fetchers.httpx.AsyncClient\",\n        lambda **kw: httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler), **kw))\n    result = await run(cfg, dry_run=False)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 1, \"changed\": 0}\n    # run again: same job should now be neither new nor changed\n    result2 = await run(cfg, dry_run=False)\n    assert result2 == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\nAlso worth one for `agent.py`'s `db-new`/`db-mark` cycle against a real pipeline run (scan marker only advances on explicit `db-mark`, never on `db-new` — this invariant is the crux of the scan workflow and is currently unverified).\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "Priority if coverage work is scoped incrementally",
        "content": "1. `filters.py` + `models.py` — pure functions, cheap, high logic density (dedup/hash/date parsing bugs are silent and compound over time).\n2. `store.py` — SQLite dedup is the source of truth; a bug here means duplicate or lost notifications.\n3. `notify.py` `dispatch()` error isolation — one flaky webhook shouldn't silently kill Twilio/email.\n4. `fetchers.py` parser functions (pure, no network) — each `parse_*` is a brittle contract with an external API; these break silently when a vendor changes JSON shape, and only tests catch it before a bad prod run.\n5. `fetchers.py` pagination/retry loops — need mocked HTTP, more setup, but termination bugs here mean either infinite loops or silently truncated job lists.\n6. `agent.py` — CLI helpers and PDF rendering, more OS-dependent/harder to unit test cleanly (subprocess/Chrome).",
        "level": 3
      }
    ],
